                <h1>Founders of Omega Psi Phi: A Legacy of Brotherhood</h1>
                <p>Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Inc. was founded on November 17, 1911, at Howard University by Bishop Edgar Amos Love, Professor Ernest Everett Just, and Doctor Oscar James Cooper. These visionary leaders aimed to promote brotherhood, academic excellence, and community service. Their legacy continues to thrive in the values and mission of the fraternity today.</p>
